ature. This branch is plausible as a diversity-generating route, not a high-confidence targeted uracil pathway.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_003\",\n        \"rxn_017\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Expand DAMN conversion through identified intermediates rather than assigning direct uracil/cytosine outputs.\",\n        \"Present this as low-yield exploratory systems chemistry unless exact product evidence is available.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P8\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_003\": 0.32,\n        \"rxn_018\": 0.72\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.58,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.64,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.69,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.75,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.64,\n      \"feedback\": \"The literature does support cyanide polymerization under alkaline hydrothermal or subaerial vent-like conditions yielding uracil and orotic acid among pyrimidines. However, this network labels the route as hydrothermal while the cited work is more specific to alkaline, moderate-temperature conditions rather than classic high-temperature vent chemistry. The step is too coarse and depends on questionable prior HCN generation.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_003\",\n        \"rxn_018\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Specify moderate alkaline vent or subaerial hydrothermal conditions around 80C rather than generic hydrothermal.\",\n        \"Distinguish cyanide polymerization product mixtures from directed uracil synthesis.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P9\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_019\": 0.87,\n        \"rxn_020\": 0.88\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.86,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.83,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.85,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.89,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.86