nce >= 0.9\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Uracil\nOVERALL STRATEGY: This network treats uracil synthesis as a literature-grounded systems problem rather than a single linear route. It uses experimentally supported terrestrial routes centered on cyanoacetylene/cyanoacetaldehyde, concentrated urea, formamide thermochemistry, \u03b2-alanine + urea condensation, cyanide polymerization under moderate alkaline hydrothermal-like settings, ice-eutectic cyanide chemistry, and extraterrestrial delivery. It also includes the Powner-Sutherland bypass as a connected uracil-related branch that converges on uridine nucleotide chemistry without incorrectly forcing free uracil release. Hydrothermal nodes supply reduced carbon feedstocks and concentration mechanisms that feed surface chemistry, while surface products feed biochemical assembly of uridine phosphate and uridine oligomers.\n\nMOLECULES (27 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: CH2O2 (formic acid/formate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_004: CH3NO (formamide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: CHN (HCN) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: C3HN (cyanoacetylene) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_007: CHNO (cyanate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_008: CH4N2O (urea) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C3H2N2O (cyanovinylurea ensemble) [intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C3H2N2O (cyanoacetaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C4H5N3O (cytosine) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C4H4N2O2 (uracil) [target]\n  - mol_013: C4H4N4 (DAMN) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_014: C3H7NO2 (beta-alanine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_015: C4H6N2O2 (dihydrouracil) [intermediate]\n  - mol_016: C2H4O2 (glycolaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_017: CH2N2 (cyanamide) [intermediate]\n  - mol_018: C3H6O3 (glyceraldehyde) [intermediate]\n  - mol_019: C3H4N2O (2-aminooxazole) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mo