74,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.75,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.78,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.73,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.74,\n      \"feedback\": \"HCN tetramerization to DAMN is robust and very well supported. The subsequent conversion of DAMN to uracil and cytosine under photothermal conditions is much less established as a selective route; literature supports pyrimidine derivatives from DAMN chemistry, but not a clean direct uracil pathway. Good as a branching systems-chemistry node, weaker as a defined synthesis pathway.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_012\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Present DAMN as a branch point to mixed heterocycles rather than a direct uracil route\",\n        \"Include lower confidence language and product-mixture caveats\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P8\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_013\": 0.86\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.85,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.84,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.88,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.84,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.85,\n      \"feedback\": \"This pathway aligns well with recent literature on cyanide polymerization under moderate alkaline hydrothermal-like or subaerial hot conditions yielding pyrimidines including uracil and orotic acid. It is chemically credible and environmentally relevant, though product distributions are broad and not highly selective.\",\n      \"approved\": true,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Specify moderate conditions clearly as around 80C and 1 bar rather than generic hydrothermal settings\",\n        \"Indicate uracil as part of a pyrimidine mixture rather than exclusive product\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P9\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_014\": 0.83,\n        \"rxn_010\": 0.92\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.84,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.82,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.9,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.87,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.85,\n      \"feedback\": \"The ice eutectic cyanide-urea branch is well aligned with literature showing pyrimidine formation in frozen concentrated systems. The route is somewhat generalized in stoichiometry and products, but the environmental logic is strong and the cytosine-to-uracil continuation is sound.\",\n      \"approved\": true,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"State frozen eutectic conditions explicitly and emphasize mixture-based outcomes\",\n        \"Separate direct uracil formation from cytosine formation if quantitative fidelity is needed\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P10\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_015\": 0.89,\n        \"rxn_016\": 0.88\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.89,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.88,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.91,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.89,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.89,\n      \"feedback\": \"A strong surface-pool route consistent with Chittenden-Schwartz dry-down chemistry and UV conversion of dihydrouracil to uracil. This is one of the more geochemically coherent non-cyanoacetylene pathways in the network and properly exploits wet-dry cycling and UV exposure.\",\n      \"approved\": true,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Add montmorillonite explicitly to the reaction description if not already in the underlying metadata\",\n        \"Clarify mild heating and evaporation regime\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"best_pathway_id\": \"P2\",\n  \"overall_confidence\": 0.86,\n  \"network_feedback\": \"This is a strong, well-connected synthesis network with excellent breadth and good literature awareness. Topologically it exceeds requirements: it has many molecule and reaction nodes, multiple convergent routes to